<TITLE> Court to give Sheikh Helal verdict on Feb 24 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 17 (bdnews24.com)  The verdict on a case against Sheikh Helaluddin and his wife Rupa Chowdhury, accused of amassing wealth by unfair means, will be delivered on Feb 24. Judge Tanjina Ismail gave the verdict date Sunday at the Special Judge's Court-6 set up at the Jatiya Sangsad complex to expedite cases of corruption. Anticorruption Commission deputy director Manjurul Ahmed filed the case at Ramna Police Station on Sep 24, 2007, accusing Helal of hiding information about property worth Tk 7.60 crore. His wife stands accused of assisting him. Sheikh Helal submitted his wealth statement to the ACC on June 6 last year. According to the statement, he claimed to own Tk 8.48 lakh in property and assets. On Jan 15, investigation officer and assistant director of the ACC, Syed Ahmed submitted the chargesheet saying the accused owned assets totalling Tk 16.22 crore. On Feb 12, a Dhaka court convicted Sheikh Helal in an extortion case and sentenced him to seven years. Both the accused are on the run. bdnew
